<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
To prevent the inability of passengers to exit the airplane in the event of an emergency, accomplish the following:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) For airplanes having serial numbers 7004 through 7028, inclusive: Within 14 days after the effective date of this
AD, and thereafter at intervals not to exceed 3 days until the action required by paragraph (e)(2) of this AD is accomplished,
apply an anti-
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
icing agent to the operating mechanisms of the passenger door in accordance with Canadair Alert Service Bulletin
No. S.B. A601R&hyph;52&hyph;002, Revision `C,' dated December 1, 1993.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
